fields.name: Smart Blend 10-10-10
fields.description: Our most popular all-purpose fertilizer with balanced NPK ratio. Perfect for vegetables, flowers, and general garden use. Provides steady nutrition throughout the growing season.
fields.dosage_info: Apply 2-3 pounds per 100 square feet. Mix into soil before planting or side-dress established plants every 4-6 weeks during growing season.

fields.name: Green Boost 20-5-10
fields.description: High nitrogen formula designed for lush, green foliage. Ideal for lawns, leafy vegetables, and ornamental plants that need vigorous vegetative growth.
fields.dosage_info: Apply 1-2 pounds per 100 square feet. For lawns, apply every 6-8 weeks during active growth. Water thoroughly after application.

fields.name: Root Master 5-20-10
fields.description: Phosphorus-rich formula that promotes strong root development and early plant establishment. Excellent for transplanting and starting new gardens.
fields.dosage_info: Apply 1.5-2 pounds per 100 square feet at planting time. Mix into root zone. Reapply every 8-10 weeks for established plants.

fields.name: Bloom Pro 10-30-20
fields.description: Premium flowering formula with high phosphorus content. Encourages abundant blooms and fruit set. Perfect for flowering plants, tomatoes, and fruit trees.
fields.dosage_info: Apply 1-2 pounds per 100 square feet when flower buds appear. Repeat every 3-4 weeks during flowering period. Avoid over-application.

fields.name: Fruit Power 5-10-30
fields.description: High potassium formula designed for fruit development and overall plant health. Improves fruit quality, size, and disease resistance.
fields.dosage_info: Apply 2-3 pounds per 100 square feet during fruit development stage. For fruit trees, apply in early spring and again after fruit set.

fields.name: Veggie Supreme 15-15-15
fields.description: Specially formulated for vegetable gardens. Balanced nutrition supports healthy growth from seedling to harvest. Works great for tomatoes, peppers, and squash.
fields.dosage_info: Apply 2 pounds per 100 square feet at planting. Side-dress with 1 pound per 100 square feet every 4 weeks during growing season.
